&lt;p&gt;Better Births Midwife Band: 8 a&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time: Fixed term or secondment for one year with potential to extend&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maternity services at Buckinghamshire Healthcare NHS Trust are undergoing transformational change in line with the ambitions set out in Better Births, The NHS Long Term Plan and the need to address health inequalities that exist particularly for women and birthing individuals from BAME backgrounds and high risk groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is aligned with the national and Local Maternity System (LMS) deliverables and we are looking for an exceptional midwife to join the team to ensure our maternity services become even safer, kinder, more personalised and family friendly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our aim is that every woman and birthing individual that will be provided personalised care; better postnatal and perinatal mental health care and that continuity of carer will be implemented for a minimum of 35% of women in Buckinghamshire by March 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A key focus of this role will be the leadership, engagement, support, education and practice development of staff to deliver the new models of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join Buckinghamshire Healthcare NHS Trust supporting the senior midwifery management team to deliver the maternity transformation plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Heidi Beddall (HOM) 01296 316127 or Julie Everett (PA) 01296 316142 (Tuesdays and Wednesdays only)&lt;/p&gt;
